summaries.title: Microaggressions and Invisible Labor in Group Dynamics
summaries.summaryText: Aaliyah recounted repeated experiences of having her technical input questioned in group settings. She also described taking on emotional labor to support other students facing similar bias. [Part 2/4]

summaries.title: Community and Peer Mentorship as Anchors
summaries.summaryText: Peer mentors and cultural centers helped Luis navigate isolation as a first-gen Latino student. [Part 1/4]

summaries.title: Balancing Pressure, Pride, and Belonging
summaries.summaryText: Daniel expressed pride in representing his familys aspirations but also noted ongoing struggles with imposter syndrome. He values belonging through peer groups that normalize his experiences as a first-gen student of color in STEM. [Part 2/4]

summaries.title: Navigating Gender Bias in Research Environments
summaries.summaryText: She recounted experiences where her technical contributions were overlooked and strategies she used to assert confidence. [Part 2/4]

areasForImprovement.title: Expand Peer Mentoring for First-Generation STEM Students
areasForImprovement.description: Formalize mentoring programs that pair upperclassmen with first-generation students early in their academic journey. These networks reduce imposter syndrome and improve retention rates. [Extended 1]
actionItems: Create opt-in mentoring tracks for first-gen students
Provide mentor training focused on inclusive communication

areasForImprovement.title: Formal Recognition for Student Advocacy and Mentorship Work
areasForImprovement.description: Students like Aaliyah contribute substantial unpaid labor in mentoring and advocacy roles. Institutions should recognize these contributions as part of leadership and service learning frameworks. [Extended 4]
actionItems: Create service-learning credit for mentorship and advocacy roles
Include advocacy experience in leadership award criteria

areasForImprovement.title: Broaden Access to Early Engineering Exposure Programs
areasForImprovement.description: Ethans reflection highlights unequal early access to STEM exposure. Partnering with local schools and community programs can help level the playing field for underrepresented groups. [Extended 4]
actionItems: Create summer bridge programs for high school students
Offer needs-based scholarships for pre-college engineering camps

areasForImprovement.title: Normalize Academic Struggle Through Faculty Messaging
areasForImprovement.description: Faculty can help counter imposter syndrome by sharing personal learning experiences, highlighting that mastery develops over time and through mistakes. [Extended 3]
actionItems: Encourage faculty to include learning journeys in course introductions
Develop short workshops on inclusive teaching practices
